¸à¥à¤¤à¤° à¤•à¤¾à¤¯à¤® à¤—à¤°à¥à¤¨à¥‡ à¤šà¥à¤¨à¥Œà¤¤à¤¿,</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>à¥ª.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;à¤…à¤¨à¥Œà¤ªà¤šà¤¾à¤°à¤¿à¤• à¤…à¤°à¥à¤¥à¤¤à¤¨à¥à¤¤à¥à¤° à¤° à¤›à¤¾à¤¯à¤¾à¤ à¤¬à¥ˆà¤‚à¤•à¤¿à¤™à¤•à¤¾ à¤•à¤¾à¤°à¤£&nbsp;BFIs&nbsp;à¤•à¥‹ à¤¸à¤®à¤—à¥à¤° à¤µà¥à¤¯à¤¾à¤œà¤¦à¤° à¤•à¤® à¤—à¤°à¥€ à¤•à¥‹à¤­à¤¿à¤¡à¤²à¥‡ à¤¥à¤²à¤¿à¤¨ à¤²à¤¾à¤—à¥‡à¤•à¥‹ à¤…à¤°à¥à¤¥à¤¤à¤¨à¥à¤¤à¥à¤°à¤®à¤¾ à¤•à¤® à¤¸à¥à¤°à¥‹à¤¤ à¤²à¤¾à¤—à¤¤à¤®à¤¾ à¤²à¤—à¤¾à¤¨à¥€ à¤µà¥ƒà¤¦à¥à¤§à¤¿ à¤—à¤°à¥à¤¨à¥‡ à¤šà¥à¤¨à¥Œà¤¤à¤¿,</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>à¥«.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;à¤¬à¤¢à¥à¤¦à¥‹ à¤¡à¤¿à¤œà¤¿à¤Ÿà¤² à¤…à¤°à¥à¤¥à¤¤à¤¨à¥à¤¤à¥à¤°à¤®à¤¾ à¤¸à¥‚à¤šà¤¨à¤¾ à¤ªà¥à¤°à¤µà¤¿à¤§à¤¿ à¤¸à¤®à¥à¤¬à¤¨à¥à¤§à¥€ à¤œà¥‹à¤–à¤¿à¤® à¤° à¤¸à¥‹ à¤œà¥‹à¤–à¤¿à¤® à¤µà¥à¤¯à¤µà¤¸à¥à¤¥à¤¾à¤ªà¤¨ à¤—à¤°à¥à¤¨ à¤‰à¤šà¥à¤š à¤¸à¥‚à¤šà¤¨à¤¾ à¤ªà¥à¤°à¤µà¤¿à¤§à¤¿à¤•à¥‹ à¤–à¤°à¥à¤š,</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>à¥¬.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;à¤¨à¥‡à¤ªà¤¾à¤² à¤œà¤¸à¥à¤¤à¥‹ à¤¸à¤¾à¤¨à¥‹ à¤…à¤°à¥à¤¥à¤¤à¤¨à¥à¤¤à¥à¤°à¤®à¤¾ à¤…à¤¤à¥à¤¯à¤§à¤¿à¤•&nbsp;BFIs&nbsp;à¤•à¥‹ à¤¸à¤‚à¤–à¥à¤¯à¤¾ à¤¹à¥à¤à¤¦à¤¾ à¤¬à¥‡à¤²à¤¾à¤¬à¥‡à¤²à¤¾à¤®à¤¾ à¤…à¤¸à¥à¤µà¤¸à¥à¤¥ à¤ªà¥à¤°à¤¤à¤¿à¤¸à¥à¤ªà¤°à¥à¤§à¤¾ à¤¹à¥à¤¨à¥‡ à¤—à¤°à¥‡à¤•à¥‹,</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>à¥­.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;à¤ªà¤°à¤¿à¤¯à¥‹à¤œà¤¨à¤¾à¤•à¥‹ à¤…à¤µà¤¸à¥à¤¥à¤¾ à¤­à¤¨à¥à¤¦à¤¾ à¤§à¤¿à¤¤à¥‹à¤•à¥‹ à¤†à¤§à¤¾à¤°à¤®à¤¾ à¤•à¤°à¥à¤œà¤¾ à¤²à¤—à¤¾à¤¨à¥€ à¤—à¤°à¥à¤¨à¥‡ à¤ªà¥à¤°à¤µà¥ƒà¤¤à¥à¤¤à¤¿ à¤•à¤¾à¤¯à¤®à¥ˆ à¤°à¤¹à¥‡à¤•à¥‹,&nbsp;à¤†à¤¦à¤¿ à¥¤à¤¯à¤¸à¤°à¥€ à¤µà¤°à¥à¤¤à¤®à¤¾à¤¨ à¤…à¤µà¤¸à¥à¤¥à¤¾à¤®à¤¾ à¤•à¥‹à¤­à¤¿à¤¡ à¥§à¥¯ à¤•à¥‹ à¤®à¤¹à¤¾à¤®à¤¾à¤°à¥€à¤²à¥‡ à¤¸à¤®à¤—à¥à¤° à¤…à¤°à¥à¤¥à¤¤à¤¨à¥à¤¤à¥à¤°à¤¸à¤à¤—à¥ˆ&nbsp;BFIs&nbsp;à¤²à¤¾à¤ˆ à¤ªà¤¨à¤¿ à¤¨à¤°à¤¾à¤®à¥à¤°à¥‹ à¤…à¤¸à¤° à¤—à¤°à¥‡à¤•à¥‹ à¤¦à¥‡à¤–à¤¿à¤¨à¥à¤› à¥¤ à¤µà¤°à¥à¤¤à¤®à¤¾à¤¨ à¤…à¤µà¤¸à¥à¤¥à¤¾ à¤° à¤šà¥à¤¨à¥Œà¤¤à¤¿ à¤¹à¥‡à¤°à¥à¤¦à¤¾ à¤¬à¥ˆà¤‚à¤•à¤¹à¤°à¥à¤¬à¥€à¤š à¤®à¤°à¥à¤œà¤° à¤ªà¥à¤°à¤•à¥ƒà¤¯à¤¾ à¤¯à¤¥à¤¾à¤¶à¤¿à¤˜à¥à¤° à¤°à¥à¤ªà¤®à¤¾ à¤…à¤˜à¤¿ à¤¬à¤¢à¤¾à¤‡ à¤¬à¤¢à¥à¤¦à¥‹ à¤ªà¥à¤°à¤µà¤¿à¤§à¤¿ à¤¤à¤¥à¤¾ à¤…à¤¨à¥à¤¯ à¤¸à¤‚à¤šà¤¾à¤²à¤¨ à¤²à¤¾à¤—à¤¤ à¤•à¤® à¤—à¤°à¥à¤¦à¥ˆ à¤¡à¤¿à¤œà¤¿à¤Ÿà¤² à¤¬à¥ˆà¤‚à¤•à¤¿à¤™à¤²à¤¾à¤ˆ à¤¬à¤²à¤¿à¤¯à¥‹ à¤°à¥à¤ªà¤®à¤¾ à¤ªà¥à¤°à¥‹à¤¤à¥à¤¸à¤¾à¤¹à¤¿à¤¤ à¤—à¤°à¥à¤¨ à¤¸à¤°à¤•à¤¾à¤°,&nbsp;à¤¨à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾à¤®à¤• à¤¨à¤¿à¤•à¤¾à¤¯ à¤°&nbsp;BFIs&nbsp;à¤¸à¥à¤µà¤¯à¤‚à¤²à¥‡ à¤ªà¤¨à¤¿ à¤§à¥à¤¯à¤¾à¤¨ à¤¦à¤¿à¤¨ à¤œà¤°à¥à¤°à¥€ à¤› à¥¤</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>English</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Answer: The modern banking history of Nepal is believed to have started after the establishment of Nepal Bank Limited in 1994. At present , Nepal Rastra Bank ( NRB) is the regulatory body for BFIs conducting banking transactions using the powers conferred by the Banking and Financial Institutions ( BFIs) Act, 2073 ( BAFIA) .&nbsp;<em><strong>The current situation of BFIs as at Ashadh end 2078 as published by NRB are:</strong></em>1. There are 27 \"A\" class, 18 \"B\" class, 17 \"C\" class, 70 \"D\" class and 1 Infrastructure Development Bank in Nepal with their 10,683 branches in total.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>2. Among the 753 local authorities 750 local bodies have the presence of commercial banks.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>3. Similarly, the total deposits of BFIs is more than Rs. 47 kharba and loan outstanding is more than Rs. 41 Kharba.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>4 . Deposit to GDP and Credit to GDP of BFIs is around 111% and 98% respectively.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>5 . Weighted average interest rate on deposits and credit is 4.76%&nbsp; and 8.43% respectively.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>6 . Similarly, there are more than 3.77 crore deposit accounts and 17 lakh loan accounts.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>7. There are more than 1.4 crore mobile banking customers which is much more than in the past.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>8 . Similarly, the NPL of overall BFIs is 1.48%.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nepal\'s current banking challenges can be documented as follows:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>1. The slowdown in the overall world economy and Nepal\'s economy due to the pandemic caused by COVID-19 has affected the quantitative and qualitative growth of banking transactions,&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>2. Due to COVID-19, there is a high risk of bad loans in various businesses such as tourism, luxury industries and many other loans/advances.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>3. The pandemic of Covid-19 have&nbsp;degraded the quality of credit of BFIs.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>4. The challenge of increasing credit disbursement by lowering the overall lending interest rates while competing for deposit collection at a lower rate where there is existence of informal economy and shadow banking,&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>5. Information technology risks in a growing digital economy and the high cost of information technology to manage those risks,&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>6. In a small economy like Nepal , when there are too many BFIs , there is unhealthy competition from time and again.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>7. The tendency to invest in loans on the basis of collateral rather than the condition of the project persists, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thus, in the current situation, the pandemic of Covid 19 seems to have adversely affected the overall economy as well as BFIs . Given the current situation and challenges, the government, regulators and BFIs themselves need to focus on promoting digital banking while speeding up the merger process between banks, reducing technology and other operating costs .</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Current Banking Status and Challenges (Krishna Niraula, CA)', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'current-banking-status-and-challenges-krishna-niraula-ca__trashed', '', '', '2021-10-24 09:16:11', '2021-10-24 09:16:11', '', 0, 'http://localhost/krishnablog/?p=65', 0, 'post', '', 0),
