à¥‹ à¤…à¤¸à¥à¤²à¥€ à¤•à¤¾à¤°à¤¬à¤¾à¤¹à¥€ à¤°à¥‹à¤•à¥à¤¨ à¤¨à¤ªà¤¾à¤‰à¤¨à¥‡</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Â·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;à¤‹à¤£ à¤¨à¤¤à¤¿à¤°à¥à¤¨à¥‡ à¤—à¥à¤°à¤¾à¤¹à¤•à¤²à¤¾à¤ˆ à¤•à¤¾à¤²à¥‹à¤¸à¥‚à¤šà¤¿à¤®à¤¾ à¤°à¤¾à¤–à¥à¤¨&nbsp;BFI&nbsp;à¤²à¥‡ à¤•à¤°à¥à¤œà¤¾ à¤¸à¥‚à¤šà¤¨à¤¾ à¤•à¥‡à¤¨à¥à¤¦à¥à¤°à¤®à¤¾ à¤²à¥‡à¤–à¥€ à¤ªà¤ à¤¾à¤‰à¤¨à¥à¤ªà¤°à¥à¤¨à¥‡</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Â·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;à¤•à¤°à¥à¤œà¤¾ à¤…à¤¸à¥à¤² à¤¹à¥à¤¨ à¤¨à¤¸à¤•à¥‡à¤®à¤¾ à¤µà¤¿à¤¦à¥‡à¤¶à¤¸à¥à¤¥à¤¿à¤¤ à¤…à¤¨à¥à¤¯ à¤¸à¤®à¥à¤ªà¤¤à¥à¤¤à¤¿à¤¬à¤¾à¤Ÿ à¤ªà¤¨à¤¿ à¤•à¤°à¥à¤œà¤¾ à¤…à¤¸à¥à¤² à¤‰à¤ªà¤° à¤—à¤°à¥à¤¨ à¤¸à¤•à¤¿à¤¨à¥‡</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Â·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;à¤¸à¤¬à¥ˆ à¤•à¤¾à¤°à¤¬à¤¾à¤¹à¥€à¤²à¥‡ à¤ªà¤¨à¤¿ à¤•à¤°à¥à¤œà¤¾ à¤…à¤¸à¥à¤² à¤¹à¥à¤¨ à¤¨à¤¸à¤•à¥‡ à¤°à¤¾à¤¹à¤¦à¤¾à¤¨à¥€ à¤°à¥‹à¤•à¥à¤•à¤¾ à¤¸à¤®à¥‡à¤¤ à¤°à¤¾à¤–à¥à¤¨ à¤°à¤¾à¤·à¥à¤Ÿà¥à¤° à¤¬à¥ˆà¤‚à¤• à¤®à¤¾à¤°à¥à¤«à¤¤ à¤¸à¤°à¤•à¤¾à¤°à¤²à¤¾à¤ˆ à¤ªà¤ à¤¾à¤‰à¤¨ à¤¸à¤•à¤¿à¤¨à¥‡</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Â·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;à¤•à¤°à¥à¤œà¤¾ à¤…à¤¸à¥à¤²à¥€ à¤•à¤¾à¤°à¤¬à¤¾à¤¹à¥€à¤•à¥‹ à¤•à¤¾à¤°à¤£à¤¬à¤¾à¤Ÿ à¤…à¤¨à¥à¤¯ à¤•à¤¾à¤¨à¥‚à¤¨à¥€ à¤•à¤¸à¥‚à¤°à¤®à¤¾ à¤•à¤¾à¤°à¤¬à¤¾à¤¹à¥€à¤®à¤¾ à¤°à¥‹à¤• à¤²à¤—à¤¾à¤à¤•à¥‹ à¤®à¤¾à¤¨à¤¿à¤¨à¥‡ à¤›à¥ˆà¤¨</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>à¤¯à¤¸à¤°à¥€&nbsp;BAFIA&nbsp;à¤•à¥‹ à¤ªà¤°à¤¿à¤šà¥à¤›à¥‡à¤¦ à¥® à¤®à¤¾ à¤•à¤°à¥à¤œà¤¾ à¤²à¤—à¤¾à¤¨à¥€ à¤° à¤…à¤¸à¥à¤²à¥€à¤•à¤¾ à¤µà¤¿à¤­à¤¿à¤¨à¥à¤¨ à¤ªà¥à¤°à¤¾à¤µà¤§à¤¾à¤¨ à¤°à¤¹à¥‡à¤•à¤¾ à¤›à¤¨à¥ à¥¤</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>1. Write the provisions of credit disbursement &amp; recovery as per the BAFIA, 2073.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Ans: Chapter 8</strong>&nbsp;of BAFIA has following major provisions regarding credit disbursement &amp; recovery</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Sec. 55:</strong>&nbsp;Credit investment provisions to be followed by BFIs</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Â·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Loan should be disbursed only after disclosing the purpose, subject to the credit policy determined by the NRB Directive and the Board of Directors</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Â·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Loans should be secured by collateral or appropriate guarantee for disbursement &amp; in a way that protects BFI\'s &amp; depositors\' interest</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Â·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Collateral shall be registered/transferred/withheld in BFI\'s name and sent in writing to the concerned office so that it cannot be in someone else\'s name and the concerned office should do the same accordingly.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Â·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Lending towards deprived and productive sector shall be as specified by NRB</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Â·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The terms, conditions and interest of the loan shall be as mentioned in the loan deed or contract</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Â·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Necessary proof of identity of all borrower, guarantor, directors of firm companies, shareholders holding more than specified shares by NRB, family, beneficiaries shall also be taken.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Â·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Information of Loan amount, interest, penalty, installment repayment schedule shall be given clearly to the borrower and guarantor in writing.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Â·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;BFI shall provide details of principal payable or paid, interest, penalty, fees &amp; loan deed as demanded by the borrower.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Sec. 56:</strong>&nbsp;BFIs shall monitor utilization of credit amount</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Sec. 57:</strong>&nbsp;Rights of BFIs regarding debt recovery</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Â·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If the Borrower does not comply with the terms of the loan or does not repay the loan, interest, penalty within timeframe or misuses the loan, BFI may sell the securities in auction or recover from other arrangements.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Â·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;BFI may direct borrower to keep additional collateral security within a certain period of time if he relinquishes the right of collateral to someone or the value of collateral decreases and in case of failure of borrower, BFI may recover principal &amp; interest from other movable and immovable property.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Â·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If the bank recovers principal, interest, penalty from auction sale or other arrangements, the remaining amount should be returned to the debtor.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Â·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;BFI shall send a letter to the concerned office to transfer ownership in the name of the person buying the property at auction or in BFI\'s own name if not sold in auction &amp; the office shall do accordingly.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Â·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In case of refusal or obstruction in possession of collateral by the previous owner, the concerned government body shall take action to allow possessory right .</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Â·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;No one shall be allowed to stop the recovery of written off loan made as per prevailing Credit Write off Byelaws.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Â·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;BFI shall send a letter to the credit information center to blacklist the default borrower.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Â·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Credit may also be recovered from other assets in abroad</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Â·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If all the actions fail to recover the loan, the passport may be withhold or confiscate through NRB &amp; forwarded the request to government.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Â·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Proceedings for other legal offenses shall not be deemed to have been stopped due to credit recovery proceedings.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thus, Chapter 8 of BAFIA has various provisions for credit disbursement and recovery.<a></a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Credit Disbursement and Recovery in BAFIA', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'credit-disbursement-and-recovery-in-bafia', '', '', '2021-10-24 09:18:05', '2021-10-24 09:18:05', '', 0, 'http://localhost/krishnablog/?p=161', 0, 'post', '', 0);
